00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
How can we decompose strategic business goals and get to the Structural Division?

00:05.000 --> 00:18.000
Let's talk about how we can decompose strategic business goals and get to the Structural Division.

00:18.000 --> 00:30.000
If we have about 20 goals in the corporate map, we start decomposing them with the projection of personnel and business processes.

00:30.000 --> 00:38.000
Usually, all the goals that we have stated in the projection of personnel and business processes are decomposed.

00:38.000 --> 00:49.000
We think about the activities and projects that need to be accomplished to achieve these goals, as well as the principles that need to be followed to achieve them.

00:49.000 --> 00:54.000
Let's go back to the company that works in the kitchen furniture market.

00:54.000 --> 01:02.000
In the business process section, they have a goal that sounds like an increase in the quality and functionality of the product.

01:02.000 --> 01:17.000
At the strategic planning stage, the work in the mini-groups was decided that there are 6 main ideas that will contribute to the growth of the quality and functionality of the product.

01:17.000 --> 01:21.000
The company is going to implement the quality management methods of the 6SIGM system.

01:21.000 --> 01:29.000
There is such a fashionable system 6SIGM, and some thoughts seem very good to the company, and it is going to implement it.

01:29.000 --> 01:36.000
To increase the quality and functionality of the product, it is important for the production personnel to be interchangeable.

01:36.000 --> 01:41.000
The third point is that innovations should be introduced quickly.

01:41.000 --> 01:51.000
The company does not invent innovations, it actively learns from the Italians, Germans and Scandinavians and tries to master it quickly.

01:52.000 --> 01:58.000
It is clear that high-quality products need to be equipped with high-quality components.

01:58.000 --> 02:03.000
The company needs high-tech equipment with high level of automation.

02:03.000 --> 02:12.000
The production site where it is produced already has it, but it needs to be installed on two new production sites.

02:13.000 --> 02:24.000
In addition, the company is going to develop a corporate production standard, in which all the nuances of the production of the product will be described in as much detail as possible.

02:24.000 --> 02:37.000
Typical or most common mistakes will also be indicated, which employees at different stages of production of the product can make, and which can affect the quality and functionality of the finished cuisine.

02:38.000 --> 02:50.000
The goal of improving the quality and functionality of the product was broken down into sub-goals, which can be called events, tasks, projects and principles.

02:50.000 --> 02:56.000
The second example is the same company, the same business process project.

02:56.000 --> 02:59.000
The goal is to build a strong brand.

03:00.000 --> 03:07.000
